Description:
    Generates a single MCP prompt class. Pass the prompt name and any arguments
    it should accept. The prompt name should be in snake_case format.

    This generates a prompt class in app/prompts/ that inherits from MCP::Prompt
    and includes the specified arguments.

    Arguments are optional by default. Append :required to make them required.

Example:
    `bin/rails generate mcp_prompt hotel_finder location:required check_in_date:required price_max`

    Hotel finder prompt with required location and check_in_date, optional price_max.
        Prompt: app/prompts/hotel_finder.rb

    `bin/rails generate mcp_prompt code_review code:required language:required style`

    Code review prompt with required code and language, optional style.
        Prompt: app/prompts/code_review.rb